                Assembly
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">April 16, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2334</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Bennett<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 19, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add and repeal Section 40507.2 of the Public Resources Code, relating to solid waste. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2334, as amended, Bennett.
                          Solid waste: methane reduction: working group.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law establishes the Department of Resources Recycling and Recovery, which is administered under the control of an executive officer known as the Director of Resources Recycling and Recovery.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would require the Director of Resources Recycling and Recovery to establish a working group to study the need for and value of alternative methods of methane reduction, as specified. The bill would require the working group to submit its findings and recommendations to the director on or before January 1, 2029.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.7326659669545125"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 40507.2 is added to the Public Resources Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_A116A2F7-8110-4F2C-8DCB-7FB9B22BE24A"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">40507.2.</h6> (a) The Legislature finds and declares both of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) There is a landfill crisis developing in the State of California where landfills are catching fire and smoldering for years and there is a rapid depletion of landfill capacity.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) There is a need to study this developing crisis and related issues.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) (1) The Director of Resources Recycling and Recovery shall establish a working group to study the need for and value of alternative methods of methane reduction in the event Senate Bill 54 of the 2021–22
						Regular Session and Senate Bill 1383 of the 2015–16 Regular Session are implemented as planned.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) As part of its research, the working group shall evaluate existing alternative waste disposal programs and their potential carbon capture components, including the Oslo, Norway<font color="#B30000"><strike> program</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> program,</i></font> and evaluate their applicability to the state.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) The working group’s study and any associated evaluations shall consider and be consistent with the state’s order of priority for waste management established pursuant to Section 40051.</div></i></font><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(3)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4)</i></font> The working group shall submit its findings and recommendations to the director on or before January 1, 2029.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) This section shall remain in effect only until January 1, 2030, and as of that date is repealed.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
